  "commentary": {
    "neutral_announcer_espn": "A patient battle of attrition unfolds at the net. Both teams are exchanging dinks, looking for an opening. Finally, the player in black on the near side sees an opportunity and unleashes a well-placed speed-up to win the point.",
    "hype_announcer_charged": "OHHHHHH, the kitchen is COOKING! Dinks flying left and right, a true test of nerve! BUT WAIT! The player in black sees the opening, BAM! A laser beam speed-up that nobody saw coming! POINT! GAME! SET! MATCH!",
    "coaching_breakdown": "This is a classic kitchen rally. Notice how the primary player maintains a low center of gravity and keeps the paddle face open to control the dinks. The key moment is the decision to speed up; they waited until the opponent was slightly off-balance. To improve, they could look for more angles or even a well-disguised drop shot earlier in the rally.",
    "social_media_caption": "Kitchen battle royale! \ud83d\udc51 Dinks, dinks, and a decisive speed-up! #pickleball",
    "social_media_hashtags": [
